          p
          
            ∗
          
        
        )
        −
        
          C
          
            x
          
        
        (
        
          p
          
            i
          
        
        )
        )
      
    
    {\displaystyle \max \sum _{i=1}^{N}(C_{x}(p_{*})-C_{x}(p_{i}))}
  is the largest sum of differences in point centrality 
  
    
      
        
